        <!-- Service Description -->
        <div class="service-full-description">
          <h2>What We Provide</h2>

          <p>The social safety net is complex‚Äîhealthcare systems, benefits programs, housing agencies, substance use treatment, mental health services, job training, legal aid, and dozens of other resources exist to support people in need. Yet for someone experiencing homelessness or in crisis, navigating these systems feels impossible. Healing Roots Outreach Collective provides resource navigation‚Äîhelping people understand available resources, connecting them to services, and advocating for them as they access support. A guide who knows the system can mean the difference between accessing lifesaving resources and giving up.</p>

          <p>Our resource navigators help people apply for benefits they're eligible for‚ÄîMedicaid, Supplemental Security Income (SSI), Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI), food assistance, utility assistance, and other programs. Many people don't know they're eligible or how to apply. Our navigators explain options, help gather necessary documents, complete applications, and advocate if applications are denied. When someone receives benefits, it provides financial stability and access to healthcare. This foundation can make recovery and housing stability possible.</p>

          <p>We coordinate healthcare access for people without consistent providers. We help people understand their health conditions, navigate healthcare appointments, explain test results and treatment plans, and ensure they understand their medications. Many healthcare providers have never worked with homeless populations and may not understand the barriers people face. Our navigators bridge the gap, helping providers understand our clients and helping clients navigate healthcare systems with confidence. We also help people access specialty care‚Äîmental health services, addiction treatment, dental care, and other specialized services.</p>

          <p>Substance use treatment is essential for many people, but accessing treatment can be daunting. Treatment programs have long waitlists, requirements, and processes that are confusing. Our treatment navigators help people understand different treatment options‚Äîfrom medication-assisted treatment to inpatient rehabilitation to peer support programs‚Äîand help them access the treatments that fit their needs and goals. We also help people navigate treatment systems, provide transportation to appointments, and support treatment engagement. Treatment is most successful when someone has consistent support.</p>

          <p>We also help people navigate legal systems, access legal aid, understand rights, and address legal barriers to housing and employment. Criminal records, warrants, unpaid fines, and other legal issues can prevent people from accessing housing and employment. Our navigators help people understand their legal situations and connect them to legal services that can help. When legal barriers are addressed, people have more options for stability and employment.</p>

          <h2>Program Components</h2>
          <ul class="service-components">
            <li><strong>Benefits Navigation:</strong> Help accessing SSI, SSDI, Medicaid, food assistance, and other benefits</li>
            <li><strong>Healthcare Coordination:</strong> Support accessing primary care, specialty care, and healthcare services</li>
            <li><strong>Treatment Navigation:</strong> Help accessing substance use and mental health treatment</li>
            <li><strong>Appointment Support:</strong> Transportation and support attending appointments</li>
            <li><strong>Care Coordination:</strong> Communication with healthcare providers and case management</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Navigation:</strong> Support understanding legal issues and accessing legal services</li>
            <li><strong>Benefits Advocacy:</strong> Appeals and advocacy if benefits are denied</li>
            <li><strong>System Navigation:</strong> Help understanding and accessing community resources and services</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>How to Access Services</h2>
          <p>Our resource navigators are available through our mobile outreach team and at community locations throughout King and Pierce Counties. If you need help accessing benefits, healthcare, treatment, or other resources, <a href="index.html#contact">contact us</a> to connect with a navigator. Resource navigation is free, confidential, and available to anyone who needs support accessing services.</p>
